    <note>Sang(1) Zhengguo [18167] The funerary inscription for father-in-law, Lu(5) Cong [18165] (q.v.), has him identified as jinshi, Sang(1) Dingguo, but this must be a copyiest error--ding and zheng can easily be confused and there is no Dingguo recorded as receiving the jinshi degree. Lu(5) You's [3640] comment in his funerary inscription for Zhengguo's probable grandson, Zhuang [18169], that the two families were successively intermarried (ji hunyin), establishes the relationship between the Gaoyou Sang(1) of Northern Song with the branch that moved to Taizhou during the Southern Song. Jiangnan TZ, 119.27a (Yuanfeng jinshi, year a guess).</note>
